OL,3,COfsted's first response to
OL,4,Cheadteacher's death looked 'defensive
OL,5,Cand complacent'
OL,7,F"It increased the damage to its
OL,8,Freputation, not only externally where
OL,9,Fstakeholders could perceive this
OL,10,Fdefensiveness from media coverage, but
OL,11,Falso internally where both staff and
OL,12,Fthe board could see the difference
OL,13,Fbetween the coroner's judgments and
OL,14,Fwhat they had been told.
OL,16,F"However, it has led to a changing
OL,17,Fapproach to communications within
OL,18,FOfsted, including inviting feedback
OL,19,Fand criticism to support improved
OL,20,Fpractice."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/12
