OL,3,COfsted's first response to
OL,4,Cheadteacher's death looked 'defensive
OL,5,Cand complacent'
OL,7,F"Nevertheless, the danger is that low
OL,8,Fmorale puts further pressure on
OL,9,Fretention and the quality of
OL,10,Finspection."
OL,12,FThe review by Dame Christine ` who
OL,13,Fserved as chief inspector at Ofsted
OL,14,Ffrom 2006 until 2011 ` did not examine
OL,15,Fthe inspection of Caversham Primary
OL,16,FSchool or the judgments made.
OL,18,FIt made a series of recommendations `
OL,19,Fwhich included ensuring that Ofsted's
OL,20,Factions following the coroner's report
OL,21,Fcontinue with "a sense of urgency".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/12
