OL,3,COfsted's first response to
OL,4,Cheadteacher's death looked 'defensive
OL,5,Cand complacent'
OL,7,F"I am glad that Ofsted has accepted
OL,8,Fthe majority of Dame Christine's
OL,9,Frecommendations. I am concerned that
OL,10,FOfsted does not appear willing to
OL,11,Fconsider more independent handling of
OL,12,Fcomplaints. This would add the
OL,13,Fprospect of important external
OL,14,Fscrutiny of the conduct of Ofsted
OL,15,Finspectors and their findings.
OL,17,F"After a Big Listen, we have now been
OL,18,Fpromised big change. Ofsted can have
OL,19,Fno more excuses."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/12
