OL,3,COfsted's first response to
OL,4,Cheadteacher's death looked 'defensive
OL,5,Cand complacent'
OL,7,F"I found most of it chimed with the
OL,8,Frest of the Big Listen, and in many
OL,9,Fways set it out in a really succinct
OL,10,Fway."
OL,12,FPaul Whiteman, general secretary of
OL,13,Fschool leaders' union the NAHT, said:
OL,14,F"Change to how inspections are carried
OL,15,Fout in England is now inevitable and
OL,16,Funavoidable.
OL,18,F"We need to work towards a more humane
OL,19,Fand fair system as quickly as possible.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/12
